campaign name

pilot: add case summary surface

objective

Add --case-summary to run_pilot.sh — a read-only inspection surface that
reads case.json and receipt.json and prints a human-readable summary of the
case being processed: case ID, material, procedure type, destination country,
and routing outcome. Falls back gracefully when files are absent.
Shell/docs/test only.

files allowed to change

examples/pilot/run_pilot.sh
examples/pilot/README.md
crates/service/tests/pilot_case_summary_surface_tests.rs

Claude prompt

Add --case-summary to examples/pilot/run_pilot.sh and document it in
examples/pilot/README.md, then write source-inspection tests in
crates/service/tests/pilot_case_summary_surface_tests.rs.

The --case-summary block must:

1. Check for case.json. If absent, print an error to stderr ("no case.json
   found — expected at examples/pilot/case.json") and exit 1.

2. Resolve fields from case.json using python3 (CS_ prefix vars):
     CS_CASE_ID    — case_id (or "not found")
     CS_MATERIAL   — material (or "not found")
     CS_PROCEDURE  — procedure_type (or "not found")
     CS_COUNTRY    — destination_country (or "not found")
   All vars default to "not found" on parse failure.

3. Also read receipt.json for routing context (optional — do not exit 1 if
   receipt is absent, use "not available" as default):
     CS_MFR_ID     — routing_decision.manufacturer_id
     CS_OUTCOME    — routing_decision.outcome

4. Print the following sections in order:

   CASE SUMMARY
   ------------
   CASE
     Case ID    : <CS_CASE_ID>
     Material   : <CS_MATERIAL>
     Procedure  : <CS_PROCEDURE>
     Country    : <CS_COUNTRY>

   ROUTING
     Manufacturer : <CS_MFR_ID>
     Outcome      : <CS_OUTCOME>

   SOURCE
     case.json            : <relative path shown>
     registry_snapshot.json : <relative path shown>

5. Exit 0 after printing.

6. The block must not write any files, must not invoke $(date, must not
   perform filesystem checks beyond the initial case.json guard and the
   optional receipt.json check.

7. Add --case-summary to the --help-surface listing.

README: add ## Case Summary section (after ## Routing Rationale, before
## Command Map) with the command, a description of the three sections, and a
note that the surface reads case.json directly and does not require a pilot run.

Tests (crates/service/tests/pilot_case_summary_surface_tests.rs):
Use a case_summary_block() helper anchored on "--case-summary\""
and ending at "exit 0\nfi\n" (ASCII-safe, same pattern as other surface tests).
Write at least 35 tests covering:
  - flag present in script
  - flag appears in --help-surface
  - block exits 0
  - clean failure when case.json missing (exit 1, stderr, case.json mention)
  - CASE SUMMARY header
  - CASE section: Case ID, Material, Procedure, Country fields
  - ROUTING section: Manufacturer, Outcome fields
  - SOURCE section: case.json and registry_snapshot.json both referenced
  - receipt.json is optional (no exit 1 path for missing receipt)
  - stable section ordering: CASE before ROUTING before SOURCE
  - no filesystem writes (> "${SCRIPT_DIR})
  - no date command ($(date)
  - README: ## Case Summary section, --case-summary command,
    does-not-require-pilot-run note

test command

cd ~/projects/postcad && cargo test -p service pilot_case_summary_surface_tests -- --nocapture

commit message

